Your implementation of momentum seems off, you just add a multiple of last error, instead of adding exponentially declining contributions from the past. I think you want<p><pre><code>    double dW = alpha_ * val_[l][j] * D_[l+1][i] + beta_ * dW_[l+1][i][j];
    W_[l+1][i][j] += dW;
</code></pre>
If you want to get an output class probability, softmax is the standard way. Minimize KL-divergence instead of squared error.<p>You don&#x27;t seem to be doing any regularization. It could maybe give you better generalization.<p>I think you could get a speedup by doing your linalg with blas, I guess this would complicate the code though, making it a tradeof.<p>Training on multiple threads and averaging is a nice touch. It would be interesting to hear if (how much) it improved your results.
